Slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150}(sliced). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}. Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all).

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. When hot, add the mushrooms and cook until browned ~{3-4%minutes}.

Fill another large saucepan with the boiled water from your #kettle{} and put on high heat. Add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and the @tagliatelle{200}. Stir and cook for ~{12%minutes}. After 10 mins, stir in the @baby spinach{125} and submerge to wilt. Drain into a #colander{} when cooked.

Add the @dried Italian herbs{1/2} and the lentils to the mushrooms. Cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @finely chopped tomatoes with basil{1} and @water{100}. Stir in and add the @red wine stock paste{28} to dissolve and simmer for ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @walnuts{20}. In a #small bowl{}, mix the walnuts with the parsley, half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40} and a glug of @olive oil{a glug}.

Season the Tagliatelle with @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{} and share between your bowls. Spoon the lentil sauce on top. Finish with dollops of the parsley/nut mixture and a final sprinkling of remaining cheese.

> Looking for a tasty midweek dinner option? This Veggie Bolognese with Tagliatelle cooks in just 20 minutes for a balanced and tasty dinnertime.